# API-Football credentials for the live World Cup feed.
#
# 1. Sign up for an API-Football plan at https://www.api-football.com/
#    (the Pro tier gives 7,500 requests/day — far more than the tiered poller
#    needs; the free tier also works for occasional manual pulls).
# 2. Copy this file to .worldcup.env in the same directory:
#       cp .worldcup.env.example .worldcup.env
# 3. Paste your key after the = below (no quotes, no spaces).
# 4. Pull live data:
#       bash worldcup.sh pull
#
# .worldcup.env holds a real secret and is gitignored — never commit it.
# Without a key the feed still runs off worldcup-data.json (see the demo seed
# worldcup-data.example.json).
API_FOOTBALL_KEY=
